<br>
The figure didn't give them even a glance, as it strode thru the wide doors that suddenly seemed opened by a sharp wind.  The sound of boots clicked hard on the marble floor, as the figure moved up to the large peacock statue in the middle of the room.  <br>
<br>
The priestesses in the room stopped what they were doing and looked to the figure curiously.  Then they saw a small slender arm reach out and gently touch the breast of the peacock.  Bracers on the arm gave hint to who the figure was, at least to the elder priestesses.<br>
<br>
Slowely the fingers seemed to caress the statue and then slid away gently.  The arm curled back up into the clock, as the figure seemed to stand there...taking in the statue.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hippolyte stood there gazing at the statue.  It was something familiar..something of home.  To a woman who wasn't sure where she fit into this new world.  All Hipp knew was her heart was still amazon...but her soul belonged to the Gods.  Hipp took a long deep breath.  She wasn't sure where her path was leading her.  She had returned to Themiscrya...to see the funeral of a Vasilissa.  But, despite the death of a great amazon....all seemed well in Themiscrya.  So, why was she called there.  It was no longer her city.  And she had felt she had turned her back on them....giving herself to the call from her father to take on the world surrounding the Amazon Nation.  Hipp was no longer a Queen.  She gave it up out of shame.  She was now a warrior of war and vessel of Hera.  Slowely, Hippolyte turned her eyes catching the blue ones of a priestess.  She gave the woman a nod in respect and then turned around.  The Warrior of War walked out of the Temple....her thoughts still unsure.  Unlike anytime before.  <br>
<br>
Hipp reached up and grabbed the horn of her saddle and pulled her body onto the back of the mare.  Pulling the reigns to the side, she turned the mare around and urged her single companion quickly into the woods.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
